article.description: — David Mitchell had 13 points as Brown rolled past Salve Regina 89-59 on Tuesday night in a season opener.
article.headline: Mitchell scores 13 points as Brown dumps Salve Regina 89-59
article.linkText: Mitchell scores 13 points as Brown dumps Salve Regina 89-59
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- — David Mitchell had 13 points as Brown rolled past Salve Regina 89-59 on Tuesday night in a season opener. Paxson Wojcik had 12 points for Brown. Nana Owusu-Anane added 10 points. Kino Lilly Jr. had six assists. Cameron Collins had 18 points for the Division III Seahawks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
